Elele is within Wargadud Ward in Mandera South Constituency.





A fire that suspected Al-Shabaab militants lit in an attack in Elele, Mandera South Constituency, on December 18, 2020.
Photo credit: Manase Otsialo | Nation Media Group


Police criticised
Wardadud MCA Alinoor Derow blamed the attack on security agencies and police reservists guarding the mast took off when they were attacked, fearing for their lives.
“More than enough information had been shared with security agencies in Mandera South, on the presence of armed militants within my ward, but they failed to act,” he said.



