“We are left with one mast at Wargadud town. Without proper security, Al-Shabaab will destroy it too,” he said.





A fire that suspected Al-Shabaab militants lit in an attack in Elele, Mandera South Constituency, on December 18, 2020.
Photo credit: Manase Otsialo | Nation Media Group


Police alert
There have been reports of increased activity by the terror group in Mandera but security agencies say the situation is under control.
On Wednesday night, police officers were sent to Arabia township after it emerged that the militants had planned to attack Arabia police camp.
In an interview early in December, Mandera County Commissioner Onesmus Kyatha said security agencies were alert and aware of attacks set for the Christmas season. What started out as a small outfit has grown to become al-Shabaab’s specialised fighting force responsible for carrying out commando-style attacks. There has been a lull in large-scale incidents since the Dusit2D attack in January, 2019. The event was cancelled after the judge arrived late. Interior CS Fred Matiang'i was among leaders who went to Lee Funeral Home to condole with the family. His family says he had difficulty breathing after his lungs collapsed.